<TITLE> Police checks from 10pm to halt New Year trouble </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com) - Law enforcement agencies have taken up special overnight security measures in the capital to check any public nuisance during New Year celebrations or post-election troublemakers. Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner Naeem Ahmed has requested all to refrain from any activities that hurt 'national values and culture'. There will be police check posts on every road from 10.00pm Wednesday, said a DMP statement. Select areas of the city including Gulshan, Banani, Dhanmondi, parts of Old Dhaka and Dhaka University have been put under special police protection. Members of the Rapid Action Battalion will also be patrolling the streets through the night. The Narcotics Control Department shut down all the commercial bars in capital after 5.00pm, except those of five star hotels. Police have warned they will arrest anyone found carrying alcohol or drugs. bdnews24.co
